Another indication that the ANC is making things up as it goes along with the coronavirus lockdown is the regulation on the wearing of masks in public. With an eye on a media soundbite, an ANC apparatchik in Limpopo orchestrated the arrest of more than 30 people he found without masks when he did his “inspection” on Tuesday. The problem is that, legally, the cops had no right to arrest the alleged offenders because, even in terms of the restrictions, their conduct was not illegal. Failure to wear a mask has not been gazetted as an offence. No doubt government...